indimail-mta (2.2-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * use packetsize > 512 to avoid dkim failures for sites having long txt records (hotmail.com)
  * config-fast removed display of DESTDIR
  * svscanboot/svscan option run .svscan/run or INITCMD. Use unshare --mount option to mount private mounts like custom resolv.conf
  * svscan - run .svscan/shutdown on SIGTERM
  * added inotify program to get file system events
  * added resolvconf service
  * qmailctl bug - use sysconfdir instead of INDIMAILDIR
  * qmail-remote - use X-SMTPROUTES env variable for setting artificial smtp routes. SMTPROUTES takes precendence over X-SMTPROUTES
  * use environment variable SMTPROUTEFILE, QMTPROUTEFILE, MORESMTPROUTECDB to configure smtproutes, qmtproutes, moresmtproutes.cdb filenames
  * smtpd.c - fixed spurious error "no valid cert for gateway
  * qmail-remote.c - fix for SMTPROUTE of the form domain:x.x.x.x::penalty:max_tolerance username password
  * refactored dns_text() function in libdkim, surblfilter.c, dns_text.c, dns.c
  * dkimverify.cpp - replace strtok() with strtok_r() for thread safe operation.
  * Port for openssl 1.1.0
  * smtpd.c - replaced SSLv23_server_method() with TLS_server_method()
  * smtpd.c - fixed ifdefs for openssl 1.0.1 version.
  * qmail-remote.c replaced SSLv23_client_method() with TLS_client_method()
  * use tlsclientmethod, tlsservermethod control files only for openssl version < 1.0.1
  * qmail-smtpd, qmail-remote - improved logging of TLS method errors
  * smtpd.c qmail-remote.c - fixed readling of tlsservermethod, tlsclientmethod control file
  * smtpd.c - initialize proto.len in smtp_init()
  * qmail-showctl - fixed SIGSEGV
  * upgraded fetchmail to version 6.4.0

 -- Manvendra Bhangui <manvendra@indimail.org>  Tue, 29 Aug 2017 14:12:14 +0530
